arts.ttl: Earthquakes use first-half goal from Josef Martínez to beat San Diego 1-0
arts.sum: Josef Martínez scored early in the first half and Daniel De Sousa Britto made it stand up as the San Jose Earthquakes edged San Diego FC 1-0 on Saturday night. San Diego has two matches remaining in its first regular season and is tied with Vancouver atop the Western Conference with 57 points.
